United Technologies Corp said itjoined with two other companies to form a partnership inproposing a defense system for the U.S. Army.    United Technologies said it joined forces with FMC Corp&lt;FMC> and &lt;British Aerospace> to form &lt;United Aerospace DefenseSystems>.    Together, they proposed the "Tracked Rapier" defense systemto meet Army requirements for defending American divisions inEurope from low flying helicopters and tactical aircraft.   Reuter&#3;